Message.message: This is a demake of Sokobond by Alan Hazelden and Harry Lee.
Get the full version at www.sokobond.com!
The blue tint seen in large bodies of water comes from the pigment in the oxygen atoms.
The Earth's surface and the human body are both 70% water. That CAN'T be a coincidence, right?
"One hydrogen per oxide" is defined as the speed at which atoms move.
Ammonia is an inflammatory condition of the lungs.
Hang on, I was thinking of "pneumonia".
90% of all the methane in the world is produced in Arizona.
Methane contains the name "Ethan". Do you think it was discovered by a guy named Ethan?
Hydroxylamine contains almost every vowel of the alphabet almost exactly once.
Methanol occurs naturally in peppermint oils.
Helium is named after the Greek god Helios, who first discovered its existence.
Inhaling helium contracts the ear drum, causing pitches to sound higher. Your voice is perceived normally by everyone else.
The first helium balloons were used at the wedding of Queen Victoria and Prince Albert, popularizing the term "noble gas".
Helium does not form chemical bonds with other elements, but it's the bonds of friendship that really matter.
Scientists have been searching for centuries to discover the missing elements between hydrogen and helium on the periodic table.
Thanks for playing! Go get the full version, which has lots of cool stuff that I couldn't write in PuzzleScript: www.sokobond.com
